<h2 class="bold font-l">Dr. Nefarious' Glitching</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Dr. Nefarious has a famous trademark gag whenever he loses his temper or under extreme stress, Nefarious instantly malfunctions and freezes up to pick up radio waves of soap opera episodes of Lance and Janice until he is whacked behind the head by Lawrence or anyone else. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RunningGag" class='trope-example-link'>Running Gag</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="y5hco2" data-video-descrip="Though you wouldn't know it until the Final Boss battle. For most of the game, he's on friendly terms with Ratchet, but his uncompromising drive to undo his mistakes is what pushes him into villain territory." data-video-title="Alister Azimuth" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/y5hco2_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/y5hco2.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/BigBadFriend" data-video-tropename="Big Bad Friend" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/RatchetAndClankFutureACrackInTime" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/y5hco2.jpg">
